node.text:
By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

#NomadGrills #grillhunters #grilledlettuce #grilledsalad #vealchop #grilledvealchops #smokedveal

node.text:
from Scratch! 🇲🇦😍🍆🍅🔥
This dish is a must and the flavors are amazing!
🕌: Fez, Morocco
🎥: @foodyfetish #foodyfetishoriginal 
Tag a Friend that would love this dish!👇🏼
.

Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk.  Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness   

You can't sit there scrolling through Insta feeling that everyone else has got their lives together and you haven't if you haven't tried to do anything about it. 
 
Everyone is busy. 

This past year has been the most stressful of our lives.
 
👉 There's a lot of understandable underlying stress across the globe right now. 
 
💯 But you have the choice every day to be in control of how you think and how you act. 
 
If you know that you can't act positively and proactively to help yourself live your best life and you can't do it consistently alone, then why not consider investing in coaching? 
 
🙌 Body Smart's incredible accountability coupled with their science and psychology-based nutrition, fitness and mindset coaching really has the power to change your life forever. 
 
💪 Bold statement but they stand by it! 
 
💬 To chat about 1:1 personalised coaching with Body Smart, drop them a message with #LETSGO and they'll talk you through the process of seeing whether you're suitable for coaching and they're suitable for you.⁣

node.text:
Sweet & spicy pan fried salmon 🤤

Who’s down to try this recipe by @thatfoodiejess 

for oven version: 
* in a baking dish, put a large sheet of foil and add marinated salmon pieces and marinade
* fold ends of foil sheet to form a parcel (basically enclosing the salmon in the foil)
* bake at 190° for 10-15 (depends on thickness, for this size I usually do 12 mins)
* open up parcel to expose the top of salmon, then continue to bake for 5 minutes or until top is slightly brown. 

ingredients:

• 2 salmon slices 
• 1 tbsp oyster sauce 
• 1 1/2 tbsp light soy sauce 
• 1 tbsp brown sugar 
• 1 tsp garlic ginger paste 
• 1 tbsp water 
• 1/2 tsp chilli flakes (adjust to liking) 
• 1/2 tsp sesame oil 
• less than handful chopped coriander/cilantro 

method: 
1. mix sauce ingredients ingredients 
2. marinate salmon for at least 15 mins, best is 30 mins
3. Pan fry for total 10-12 mins, browning all sides, around 2 minutes each side then when all brown, cook remaining time with skin side down. (hope this makes sense 😅) 
4. when salmon almost done, add in marinade and coat salmon.
5. serve over rice, noodles, salad or anythinggg
